com.projetloki.genesis.image

Interface Hashable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Font, Gradient, Image, MathFunction, Shape, Shaper, TextShape, TextShape.Glyph

    public interface Hashable
    An object with a hash code of arbitrary bit length. The risk of hash collision must be so low that it can be considered to be zero. The hash function is expected to be consistent between execution runs, so it is safe to persist hash codes.

    In the context of image generation, hash codes can be used to determine very quickly if an image has already been saved to the disk during a previous execution run. This requires the hash code of the image to be saved as well, for example in the file name or as meta information.
